{
  "_comment": "Retrieval-quality benchmark queries for the cix repository. Each query is paired with paths that should rank in the top-k (expected_paths) and paths that should NOT (anti_paths). Run before/after toggling CIX_EMBED_INCLUDE_PATH and compare precision@k + anti-path leakage.",
  "_categories": {
    "concept": "Natural-language queries that describe a feature/intent, not a specific identifier.",
    "path_hint": "Queries containing words that appear in file paths (server, cli, watcher) — these benefit most from path-in-embedding.",
    "identifier": "Single-token camelCase/snake_case names that look like symbols. cix symbols already covers these; goal is no regression."
  },
  "queries": [
